> Along with the mustard-based sauce, the crispy potatoes and tender broccoli in this recipe are also great pairings for a juicy cut of beef.

Preheat your #oven{} to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Pick the @rosemary{1%unit}(leaves picked and roughly chopped).

Peel and grate the @garlic{1%unit}(peeled and grated).

Season the @Irish Beef Rump{250%g} with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw meat and its packaging.

Cut the @potatoes{600%g} into 2cm chunks (peeling optional).

Add the potatoes to a lined #baking tray{}.

Toss with half the rosemary, salt, pepper and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn the tray halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the tip of the @broccoli{1%unit}. Cut head into small florets and stem into 2cm pieces.

Pop the broccoli onto a lined baking tray.

Toss with salt, pepper and a drizzle of oil. Spread out in a single layer.

When the potatoes have been cooking for ~{15%minutes}, place the broccoli on the middle shelf of the oven and roast until crispy around the edges, ~{10-12%minutes}.

== Beef ==

Place a pan over high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, fry the beef until browned, ~{1-2%minutes} each side for medium-rare.

Cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you like it medium and a further ~{1-2%minutes} on each side if you want it well-done.

> IMPORTANT: Meat is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Once cooked, remove from pan and allow to rest.

== Mustard Rosemary Sauce ==

Return the pan to medium-low heat and add the @creme fraiche{110%g}.

Season with pepper then stir in the @beef stock{1%sachet}, garlic, half a @mustard{1/2%sachet}, and remaining rosemary.

Cook, stirring, until everything is combined and the sauce is nice and smooth, ~{3-5%minutes}.

> TIP: Loosen the sauce with a splash of @?water{to taste} if you feel it's too thick.

== To Serve ==

Thinly slice the beef and divide between plates.

Plate the broccoli and potatoes alongside.

Pour the creamy mustard rosemary sauce over the beef.